elf remarks, ‘Is he not rightly named Jacob? for he has supplanted me these two times’ (Genesis 27:36). <i>Jacob</i> is especially common as a Jewish given name, although it also became very popular among the Puritans from the 16th century onwards, and has again been widely used since the 1990s.  Compare  James ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Jakob Jakobsson Finkenberg was born in 1410, in Turku, Turku ja Pori, Finland, his father, Jakob Finken Hvittis, was 35 and his mother, Mrs Jacob Finkekn Hvittis, was 30. He had at least 1 son with Kerstin Henriksdotter. He died in 1470, in his hometown, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1410–1470":"1410–1470","1430–1472":"1430–1472","1375–1450":"1375–1450","1380–Female":"1380–Surnud","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1375":"1375","1450":"1450","1472":"1472","1470":"1470","1380":"1380","Hvittis, Turku Pori, Finland":"Huittinen, Turku ja Pori, Soome","Hvittis, Turku, Lansi-Suomen Laani, Finland":"Länsi-Suomi, Soome","Turku,Finland":"Turku, Turku ja Pori, Soome","Hvills,Turku,Pori,Finland":"Turku, Turku ja Pori, Soome"},"fi":{"1410–1470":"1410–1470","1430–1472":"1430–1472","1375–1450":"1375–1450","1380–Female":"1380–Kuollut","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1375":"1375","1450":"1450","1472":"1472","1470":"1470","1380":"1380","Hvittis, Turku Pori, Finland":"Huittinen, Turku ja Pori, Suomi","Hvittis, Turku, Lansi-Suomen Laani, Finland":"Länsi-Suomi, Suomi","Turku,Finland":"Turku, Turku ja Pori, Suomi","Hvills,Turku,Pori,Finland":"Turku, Turku ja Pori, Suomi"},"fr":{"1410–1470":"1410–1470","1430–1472":"1430–1472","1375–1450":"1375–1450","1380–Female":"1380–Décédée","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1375":"1375","1450":"1450","1472":"1472","1470":"1470","1380":"1380","Hvittis, Turku Pori, Finland":"Huittinen, Turku ja Pori, Finlande","Hvittis, Turku, Lansi-Suomen Laani, Finland":"Länsi-Suomi, Finlande","Turku,Finland":"Turku, Turku ja Pori, Finlande","Hvills,Turku,Pori,Finland":"Turku, Turku ja Pori, Finlande","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Jakob Jakobsson Finkenber